    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix stale protocol state in DMRS channel estimation for multi-antenna configurations\n\n### Summary\nThe NR UE DMRS channel estimation contained a stale protocol state bug that manifested when using multiple receive antennas. The `delay_t` structure used for time delay estimation was shared across all antenna iterations without proper reinitialization, causing delay estimates from previous antennas to contaminate subsequent antenna processing.\n\nThis led to incorrect channel estimates and potential decoding failures, particularly noticeable in high mobility scenarios with 4+ receive antennas where timing differences between antennas were significant.\n\nThe bug was introduced when the delay estimation functionality was extended to support multiple antennas but the state management was not properly updated.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/NR_UE_ESTIMATION/nr_dl_channel_estimation.c`: Moved `delay_t delay = {0};` initialization inside the antenna loop in `nr_pdsch_channel_estimation()` to ensure clean state per antenna.\n\n"
}